thread.title: Skyline swim team leads HS Top 10 performances
thread.title_full: Skyline swim team leads HS Top 10 performances | The Seattle Times

author: Seattle Times staff
title: Skyline swim team leads HS Top 10 performances
text:
1. Skyline girl’s swim team — Turned in big performances in a dual meet against Mercer Island last Tuesday, where the 200 medley relay team and freshman Sarah DiMeco (100 free) swam the state’s fastest times. DiMeco swam the 100 in 53.80 seconds and also helped the relay team finish in in 1:51.81. Danika Himes, Darian Himes and Christina Bradley were also on the relay squad. 
2. Matt Laris, Eastside Catholic football — The senior Cal commit had seven catches for 191 yards with two touchdowns in the Crusaders’ 42-14 win over O’Dea on Friday. The victory helped EC clinch the Metro Mountain Division. Laris has 32 catches for 592 yards this season with 11 TDs. 
3. Alexandra Pimental, Marysville-Getchell diving — The senior won the 3A District/State 1-meter Diving Qualifier at Marysville Pilchuck on Saturday, posting 411.15 points. Pimental finished 10th at the state meet last year. 
4. Mackenzie Floyd, Seattle Prep soccer — The freshman scored two goals in the Panthers’ 6-0 win over Bishop Blanchet on Friday. On Thursday, she had two assists to help Prep beat Chief Sealth, 5-0, and two days earlier scored twice in an 8-1 win over Nathan Hale.

Dylan Axelson, Woodinville football — Registered 14.5 tackles and two sacks in the Falcons’ 27-21 KingCo 4A win over Eastlake on Friday night. Axelson, a senior, has 55.5 tackles this season. 
6. Katelan Soth, Kentwood golf — Won medalist honors at the 4A SPSL girls golf tournament on Friday, shooting a 149 to help the Conquerors win the team title. 
7. Isaiah Williams, Kentwood football — His 161 yards rushing on 32 carries helped the Conquerors run over Kent-Meridian, 28-7, Friday night. Williams also had a touchdown and two interceptions in Kentwood’s SPSL 4A Northeast-clinching victory. 
8. Katie Mansfield, Lynnwood volleyball — Her game-high 45 digs helped the Royals beat Arlington, 3-1, last Thursday. The Royals are second in WesCo 3A with an 8-3 record. 
9. Bellevue volleyball — Upset No. 1 team in KingCo 2A/3A Mercer Island last Tuesday, with Katie Griffin recording 23 kills and 15 digs. The Wolverines are 1-20 against the Islanders dating back to 2007 according to MaxPreps. 
10. Jaiave Magalei, Lakes – Threw for a career-high 420 yards on Friday in a 31-24 league loss to Sumner. He also had a touchdown. The senior has thrown for 1,321 yards and 14 TDs this season.
